2008-02-28  Og Maciel <ogmaciel@gnome.org>

	* po/ChangeLog, po/pt_BR.po: Brazilian Portuguese translation
	updated by F√°bio Nogueira <deb-user-ba@ubuntu.com>.

2008-02-04  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c: use STATUS instead of
	EXAMINE+SEARCH for IMAP.  should be faster and (hopefully) less error-prone, and avoids a lot
	of allocations since the response length is more or less fixed (and
	small).  also better handle errors.  if we get "#### NO" from the
	STATUS request, just return 0 new messages.  that can happen if, for
	example, a folder is selected in mailwatch that is later deleted or
	unsubscribed.

2008-02-04  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* panel-plugin/mailwatch-plugin-4.2.c,
	panel-plugin/mailwatch-plugin.c, po/ca.po, po/cs.po, po/de.po,
	po/el.po, po/en_GB.po, po/eu.po, po/fi.po, po/fr.po, po/gl.po,
	po/gu.po, po/he.po, po/hu.po, po/it.po, po/ja.po, po/lv.po,
	po/pt_BR.po, po/pt_PT.po, po/ru.po, po/sq.po, po/uk.po, po/ur.po,
	po/vi.po, po/xfce4-mailwatch-plugin.pot, po/zh_TW.po: missing string
	that should be translated

2008-02-04  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* panel-plugin/mailwatch-plugin-4.2.c,
	panel-plugin/mailwatch-plugin.c, po/ca.po, po/cs.po, po/de.po,
	po/el.po, po/en_GB.po, po/eu.po, po/fi.po, po/fr.po, po/gl.po,
	po/gu.po, po/he.po, po/hu.po, po/it.po, po/ja.po, po/lv.po,
	po/pt_BR.po, po/pt_PT.po, po/ru.po, po/sq.po, po/uk.po, po/ur.po,
	po/vi.po, po/xfce4-mailwatch-plugin.pot, po/zh_TW.po: use ngettext()
	for singular/plural translation, avoid an extra string alloc

2008-01-31  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-gmail.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-pop3.c: memleaks are bad.
	freeaddrinfo() is good.

2008-01-31  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* configure.ac: use --(enable|disable)-ipv6 rather than
	--with(out)?-ipv6

2008-01-31  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* configure.ac, libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-gmail.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-pop3.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-utils.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-utils.h: use getaddrinfo() properly and
	add (untested) support for ipv6

2008-01-31  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox.h,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-utils.h, libmailwatch-core/mailwatch.h: 
	coding style fixes

2008-01-31  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-gmail.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-pop3.c: fix connection failures
	on NetBSD apparently you're only allowed to set the first four fields of the
	addrinfo struct you pass as 'hints' to getaddrinfo().  glibc seems
	to be lenient about this; other libc implementations are not.  patch
	from NetBSD guys (bug 3767)

2008-01-31  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* INSTALL, libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c,
	libmailwatch-core/mailwatch-mailbox-pop3.c: clean up some code, fix
	banner not getting completely read on connect sometimes

