2005-05-08  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* panel-plugin/Makefile.am, panel-plugin/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c,
	panel-plugin/mailwatch-utils.c, panel-plugin/mailwatch-utils.h: lots
	of IMAP overhauling.  the prefs dialog now queries the server for a
	folder tree.  connections time out after 50 seconds, regardless of
	what the OS wants to do (this may or may not be a good thing).  i need to revisit the policy of trying port 143 first, then 993,
	then 143 again.  even though 993 is officially evil (read the
	IMAP4rev1 RFC), it annoys me that it takes so long to connect to
	espresso.

