2005-05-05  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* configure.ac: add stuff.

2005-05-05  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* panel-plugin/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c: large behavior change here.
	i found that if the IMAP server is *dropping* packets on port 143
	(e.g., like espresso.foo-projects.org does), it takes over three
	minutes for the connection to time out.  this is unacceptable: if
	the panel tries to quit during this time, it'll hang until the
	connection times out (while in g_thread_join()).  so now we set the
	socket non-blocking before connect(), and then select() on the
	socket with a low timeout, over and over, until either the
	connection succeeds or fails.  we also check the GAsyncQueue between
	each select() to see if we've been instructed to quit.  also, i implemented a sort of "caching": if port 143 fails more than
	3 times in a row, it'll temporarily (for 5 hours) stop checking port
	143, and just go for 993 with a TLS negotiation.  if both 143 and
	993 fail at the same time, we assume it's a transient error and try
	the normal sequence next time.  whew.

2005-05-05  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* panel-plugin/mailwatch.h: gee, that was dumb.  fix default timeout
	#define

2005-05-05  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

	* panel-plugin/mailwatch-mailbox-imap.c: fix generally large amounts
	of stupidity on my part (hint: the IMAP timeout actually works, and
	doesn't take 1000 times as long to actually happen)

2005-05-04  Brian Tarricone <bjt23@cornell.edu>

